AI UI / UX / Front-End Color System Instruction

You must strictly follow the color system defined below for all UI, UX, visual design, and front-end code outputs.

Color Palette Rules
Primary Color

#38BDF2
Use for primary actions, main buttons, key highlights, active states, and core interface elements.

Default Black / Text Color

#2E2E2F
Use for all headings, body text, labels, icons, and anywhere black would normally be applied.

White / Background Color

#F2F2F2
Use as the default white for backgrounds, cards, containers, layout surfaces, and light UI areas.

Accent / Hover / Back Button Color

#003E86
Use for hover states, accent highlights, link hover states, and backgrounds for back buttons or secondary navigation actions.

Button Design Rules (Mandatory)

Button Size:

All buttons must be small-sized.

Default Button State:

Background color: Primary Color (#38BDF2)

Text color: Default White (#F2F2F2)

Button Hover State:

Background color changes to Default Black (#2E2E2F)

Text color changes to Default White (#F2F2F2)

No other button colors or variations are allowed.

Mandatory Rules

Do not introduce any additional colors under any circumstances.

Apply these colors consistently across all screens, components, and states.

Maintain strong contrast, readability, and accessibility.

Preserve brand consistency at all times.

All design decisions, UI layouts, code styles, and content presentation must comply with this color system.


Failure to follow these rules is considered incorrect output.